A few minutes search gave me this list.

Camels and giraffes are notoriously bad swimmers, though giraffes can usually reach the bottom and walk on it. Porcupines have buoyant hollow quills and can float, but can't swim at all. Tortoises can't swim. Prairie dogs can't swim. Owls, parrots, peacocks, and red-tailed hawks can't swim. Shih-tzus get waterlogged very easily and can't swim well. Pugs, dachshunds, bulldogs, boxers, and basset hounds (but not Buh Dogs) have weird weight distribution that keeps them from being able to swim. Gorillas and chimpanzees, oddly, can't swim well, because their bones and muscles are so dense and they normally lack a lot of body fat. Hippos just sort of float. Chinchillas are prone to getting waterlogged and drowning. Asian rhinos can swim, African rhinos can't, due to differences in bone density and levels of body fat. Toads can't swim.
